      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the hidden costs that nibble away at your payment before it even reaches the principal, much like a sneaky goblin lurking in the shadows, ready to steal your gold coins. These pesky little goblins are known as \"fees and charges,\" and they can indeed feel like a surprise attack from a goblin horde. In your student loan contract, you should be on the lookout for terms like \"origination fees,\" \"late payment fees,\" \"prepayment penalties,\" and \"service fees.\" These are the goblins that can nibble away at your hard-earned gold before it even touches the principal. Always read your contract like a treasure map, looking for any hidden traps or goblin dens that might be waiting to spring on you. And remember, knowledge is power, just like knowing the secret paths through the goblin-infested forest. By understanding these terms, you can better navigate your student loan journey and avoid those pesky goblins that like to steal your gold. Keep your eyes peeled, and you'll be able to outsmart those goblins and keep your gold safe.",
